{"source_key":"sha256-300730d11a7046aaae6c4eb40315fa44","record_index":17,"record_hash":"sha256:f0e3a8c5aa9500ec875d312369193e51d098380146bd78c48146b3792cc1cf5b","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:04:58.078Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"I’m caught up.\n\nMy take: **Agent Trail should be a PR-review product built above `but-agentlog`, not part of `but-agentlog` itself.** The doc is already pointing there, and I’d keep that line hard.\n\nThe strongest v1 shape:\n\n- `but-agentlog`: captures/redacts/stores turns, records, observed targets, related lookup.\n- `Agent Trail`: takes a PR/review/branch target and publishes a review-safe projection.\n- First link placement: **PR description or bot comment**, not check-run UI. Simpler permissions, fewer moving parts.\n- First URL model: **explicit generated snapshot per PR**, not an always-live trail. Live updating sounds nice but creates privacy and “why did this change?” weirdness immediately.\n- Main UX: **Overview, Timeline, Claims, Validation, Raw Records**. Raw transcript is evidence drill-down, not the page.\n\nThe biggest unresolved product decision is the publication boundary: before a PR gets an Agent Trail link, someone or something needs to decide exactly which sessions/turns are included and confirm the redacted projection is safe enough to share.\n\nRelevant notes:\n[agent-trail.md](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md>)  \n[Including-turns.md](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md>)  \n[handoff-design.md](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md>)","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:04:58.078Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}